Generally speaking a function or method that returns a boolean would be named to start with something like is_, has_, are_, etc.  That implies the return type and makes the intent of the code clearer.

For something like this, I'd favor is_nova_server and flipping the conditions below to check if the resource is a valid Nova server.

The check here would be..

if not is_nova_server():
   return set()
